title: Blockout Starter Pack
description: 437 Meshes for level Blockout / Greybox in Unreal, including modular assets, materials, decal, and more.
longDescription:
Discord | GitHub | Playable Demo

This asset pack includes several primitives, modular assets, props, materials, and decal to facilitate the Blockout / Greybox of a level in Unreal Engine.


Last Update v3.1:

  • V3.1 -> Release log (17 May 2024)
  • V3.0 -> Release log (11 May 2024)
  • Other Release Logs

Please note: In the v3.0 and v3.1 updates I did many path changes. You can find all detail in release logs.

technicalDetails:
Features:

  • Modular Kit
  • Blockout, Blocking, Graybox
  • Low poly
  • Procedural Material with World-Aligned Triplanar and Local-Aligned Triplanar


Texture Sizes:

  • 2048x2048
  • 128*128


Scaled to Epic skeleton: Yes.

Collision: Yes, custom, LandMesh are per-poly

Vertex Count: Varied, average 184, max 4096.

LODs: Yes, automatically generated with Lod groups.

Number of Meshes: 434

Number of Materials: 11

Number of Materials Instances: 55

Number of Textures: 18

Supported Development Platforms: All

Documentation: https://github.com/xavier150/BlockingStarterPack

 

Additional info:

For correctly snap modular mesh with angles like SM_WallRoundedCorner_400x400_45d or SM_PipeBigTurn_15d you need set rotation grid angle to 15 degrees.

The floor meshes surface is slightly raised by two centimeters to prevent Z-fighting when there is a wall placed underneath.

Small door frames fit objects up to 216 cm tall and 100 cm wide.

The sounds in the pack are free and downloadable here: Dropbox | Youtube
